I still remember a long conversation I had with him about three decades ago. I had sought to briefly interview him on the subject of youth delinquency but he turned it into a full-blown sermon on four pillars Kenyans should stick to if we were to be the great nation we aspire to be. 

That was in the 1990s. Today, Pastor White would shudder at what he saw as a worrying trend. 

 Seek God 

The very first value he said we should embrace is repentance and return to godliness. He said it couldn’t have been a mistake that founders of the Kenyan nation found it fit to open our national anthem with the words: “Oh God of all creation, bless this our land and nation.” 



