With faith and obedience to God, Pastor White said, we would be in safer hands than if we had a million-strong army or even a nuclear weapon. 

He reminds me of former US President Ronald Reagan who, in the 1980s,  came up with a grand idea to install in the American skies and those of her allies an anti-missile protective shield to permanently keep off the Russians and other potential enemies. The project, which never saw the light of day, was dubbed the Strategic Defence Initiative (SDI) or simply the Star Wars, and was to cost arm and a leg. 



