When world-famous US televangelist Bill Graham heard about it, he secured an appointment with President Reagan and told him: “Mr President, why put up such an expensive shield in the skies when our national motto ,‘In God We Trust,’ is all we need to protect us from our enemies?” 

 Parents lost in Siberia 

The second value Pastor White talked about is going back to old parenting. He regretted that though physically staying with their children, technology and the modern lifestyle has seen children live in Alaska and the parents in Siberia, under the same roof. Mark you at the time mobile phone and the tablet hadn’t arrived. 

Today, you drop in on a typical household and you will be surprised by the strangers living together in name of a family. In the living room, the father has no time to talk to the children because he is permanently fixated on the TV watching the European Premier League. 

The wife is at the far corner catching up on latest from WhatsApp groups, and each of the children is in their own world scrolling for the latest photos of their favourite influencer on social media. 

Are you surprised that  the teenagers caught in the Mountain View house of sin had been away for days and their parents unaware of their whereabouts! 



