Mark you, these days it sounds “cool” for children to call to say they are “sleeping over” at a friend’s house, a “friend” whom the parents have never met but perhaps don’t give a hoot about. 

I come from the old school and can proudly say except when in boarding school, until I was 22, there isn’t a single day my mother went to bed without knowing where I was. Even today , as an old man with my own family, when at my rural home I find it difficult to leave the compound without telling ma’am where I am going and when I will be back. 



