 Back to basics 

The third lesson from Pastor White was that Kenyans should get back to such basic little things like saying “please,”“thank you,” and “I am sorry”. Just take a sampling from wherever you are – while keeping social distance – and you will be surprised that not more than three in 10 people will utter any word of courtesy. 

 Obey the 10 Commandments 

It sounds easy but you will be surprised that though over 70 per cent of the Kenyan adult population goes to church, the last time they read the short passages containing the 10 Commandments was in Sunday school class. At that rate I wonder who will read the BBI report! 

Reading the 10 Commandments is a humbling but surest way to remind one to keep to the straight and narrow even when the spirit is willing but the fresh is weak. 



